  3,30,"On the day when every soul shall find itself presented with what it has done of good and what it has done of evil, then it will long that there were between itself and that evil a wide distance. Allah bids you beware of Himself, but Allah is gentle with H"
  3,31,"Say, \"If you love Allah then follow me, and Allah will love you and forgive you your sins, for Allah is Forgiving and Merciful"
  3,32,"Say, \"Obey Allah and the Messenger\"; but if they turn away Allah loves not disbelievers"
  3,33,"Verily, Allah has preferred Adam, and Noah, and Abraham´s family, and Imran´s family above all people"
  3,34,Offsprings one of the other. Allah Hears and Knows all things
  3,35,"When Imran´s wife said, \"Lord! I have vowed to dedicate unto Thee what is within my womb. Accept it then from me. Verily, you are Hearer and Knower"
  3,36,"And when she brought it forth she said, \"Verily, I have brought forth a female\" - Allah knew best what she brought forth; and a male is not like a female - \"I have called her Mary, and I seek a refuge in Thee for her and for her seed from"
  3,37,"And her Lord accepted fully, and gave her a goodly growth, and assigned her to Zachariah´s care. Whenever Zachariah entered her chamber he found beside her a provision, and he said, \"O Mary, whence comes this to you?\" She answered, \"I"